str2: I, the first-person pronoun. A primary pronoun of the first person I.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.

str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.

Trembling with fear, terrified. From en and tromos; terrified.

str2: To dare, endure, be bold, have courage, make up the mind. From tolma; to venture; by implication, to be courageous.
To take note of, perceive, consider carefully, discern, detect, make account of. From kata and noieo; to observe fully.
